                    <li><strong>Thumb Positioning:</strong> Place your thumb up between the index and middle fingers,
                        touching the middle segment of the middle finger. The thumb acts as a support, maintaining the
                        right angle position.</li>
                    <li><strong>Curling Other Fingers:</strong> Curl your ring and pinky fingers into your palm. They
                        should be held firmly against the palm, out of sight, to highlight the shape of the 'P'.</li>
                    <li><strong>Orientation:</strong> Rotate your hand so that the palm faces downwards, maintaining the
                        right angle and thumb position. This orientation is crucial to represent the letter 'P'
